==English==

===Adjective===
'''binary''' (''not [[comparable]]'')

# Being in a state of one of two mutually exclusive conditions, such as on or off, true or false, 6 or not 6, or the presence or absence of an electrical pulse.
#:''Binary states are often abstracted as 1 and 0 in computer science.''
# Concerning [[logic]] whose subject matter concerns binary states.
# (''arithmetic, computing'')<!--Note: templates have not been used here because they won't appear in the right format; the categories have been added to the bottom of the page--> Concerning numbers and mathematical calculations using the binary number system.
# Having two equally important parts.
#:''[[binary star]]''
#:''binary poison''
# Related to something with two parts.
#:''A '''''binary''' distribution'' is a statistical distribution with only two categories.''
# {{computing}}: Not [[ASCII]].  A collection of bytes that (potentially) contain values in the extended character range.
#:''He downloaded the '''binary''' distribution for Linux, then burned it to DVD.''

====Synonyms====
*(''arithmetic, computing''): [[base]]-2<!--the hyphen is required for the adjective-->

